nodes.bodyText:
The typical pattern here is to do:
 throw Exceptions.sneakyThrow(e);
For this reason the signature of sneakyThrow returns an exception even though the function never returns. Calling it in this way makes it clear visually that an exception will be thrown from this line and makes static analysis tools like IDEs better able to parse what is going on.

